author: Sabine Hossenfelder
description:
Learn your favorite subjects whenever and wherever you have the time with Brilliant! First 30 days are free and 20% off the annual premium subscription when you use our link ➜  https://brilliant.org/sabine. 

Physicists have reexamined a decades old quantum paradox and found a way to make quantum computers more efficient — in 37 dimensions. I set out to understand what this means and here is my best attempt at explaining it.

Paper: https://www.science.org/doi/10.1126/sciadv.abd8080
